    {
      "id": "5c9176fa-fa0e-44c8-89c0-7cdd238468cd",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Most attempts that look to use time-series representations to predict student performance seem to underwhelm. Thus, the authors propose a method to use daily-click counts to train a LSTM model to predict end-of-course performance. Comparison shows that the approach outperforms traditional approaches. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "5c9176fa-fa0e-44c8-89c0-7cdd238468cd",
        "parent": {
